if there is a matching of $G$ whose vertex set contains $X$. Show (using augmenting paths)
that the matchable sets of $G$ are the independent sets of a matroid on $V$. (We call this the
matchable sets matroid of $G$; note that this matroid has rank $2\nu(G)$). -/
```

To formalize this, we need to define the matchable sets as the independent sets of a matroid. Let's define the matchable sets matroid:

```tactics
def matchableIndepMatroid (G : Graph α β) : IndepMatroid α where
  E := V(G)
  Indep := fun S ↦ ∃ M, G.IsMatching M ∧ S ⊆ V(G, M)
  -- The empty set is matchable
  -- For any matchable set I, any subset J of I is matchable
  -- For any matchable sets I and J with |I| < |J|, there exists v in J \ I such that I ∪ {v} is matchable
  -- A set S is matchable iff it is in the matroid
