1. **Empty Set Axiom**: The empty set is trivially matchable because the empty matching matches the empty set.
2. **Subset Axiom**: If $I$ is matchable, then there exists a matching $M$ such that $I \subseteq V(G, M)$. If $J \subseteq I$, then $J \subseteq V(G, M)$ as well, so $J$ is also matchable with the same matching $M$.
