The goal is to prove `∀ (I : Set α), (∃ M, @Graph.IsMatching α β G M ∧ I ⊆ V(G, M)) → I ⊆ G.vertexSet`.
We will introduce the assumptions and then show the goal.
The hypothesis is `(∃ M, @Graph.IsMatching α β G M ∧ I ⊆ V(G, M))`. We can use `rcases` to extract the witness `M` and the properties `hM : @Graph.IsMatching α β G M` and `hI : I ⊆ V(G, M)`.
The goal is `I ⊆ G.vertexSet`.
To show this, we can use the fact that `V(G, M) ⊆ G.vertexSet`. This is a property of the definition of `V(G, M)`.
Specifically, `V(G, M)` is defined as `⋃ v ∈ M, {G.head v, G.tail v}`. Since `I ⊆ V(G, M)`, every element `i ∈ I` is in `V(G, M)`. And since `V(G, M) ⊆ G.vertexSet`, we have `i ∈ G.vertexSet`.

